================================================================================
This README could get cut & pasted to doc/Design_notes/modules/zmapServer/DASServer.html
================================================================================

A note from an email  20 Sep 2010

We originally envisaged two uses for zmap supporting das:

1) within the otterlace system we would directly access das servers that otterlace pointed us at

2) zmap could be run standalone against a das source


The former has as you point out been superceeded by pipe scripts, the latter while desireable is not straight forward and higher priorities for stand alone operation would be:

1) make zmap run really well off GFF version 2 and 3 files

2) make zmap run off an ensembl database in some way

I think we should leave the code as it is but document in a README file in the das directory that the code needs work.


================================================================================
DAS v2 Server interface

This directory implements for a DAS 2 server the routines required by the
generalised server interface defined in src/include/ZMap/zmapServerPrototype.h.

Currently there is a sample server contactable at:

	http://dev.acedb.org/das/

and also a wormbase sample server at:

	http://dev.wormbase.org/das

Requests can be sent to either of these via a browser or any other http handling
program.

For example to get a list of types of data you could issue this request:

	http://dev.acedb.org/das/wormbase/1/type




Some example queries and their replies:


http://dev.wormbase.org/das/wormbase/1/feature/processed_transcript:curated/CDS:2L52.1?format=gff


<?xml version="1.0" standalone="yes"?>

<FEATURELIST
      xmlns="http://www.biodas.org/ns/das/2.00"
      xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
      xml:base="http://dev.wormbase.org/das/wormbase/1/feature/"
      format="gff">
